modules.description: This module defines the structure and operations common to all vector spaces, including addition, scalar multiplication, and negation. It works with elements of a field (scalars) and vectors, formalizing their interactions through a set of required functions. Concrete use cases include implementing finite-dimensional vector spaces over real or complex numbers and abstracting linear algebra operations for generic fields.

This module defines the structure and operations of a commutative group, including associative addition, additive inverses, and a zero element. It works with algebraic types that support these group operations, such as integers, real numbers, or vectors. Concrete use cases include implementing cryptographic algorithms and numerical computations requiring abelian group properties.

This module provides abstractions for commutative groups and vector spaces, defining operations such as addition, negation, scalar multiplication, and identity elements. It works with algebraic structures like integers, real numbers, vectors, and fields, enforcing the necessary mathematical properties for each structure. Concrete use cases include cryptographic protocols relying on group properties and generic linear algebra implementations over arbitrary fields.
